tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic expression at variable levels in several different cell types.

subcellularLocation.summary: Mainly localized to the cell junctions. In addition localized to the nucleus.

tissueExpression.summary: Most normal tissues showed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity. Cells in CNS, lymphoid tissues, myocytes, lung, renal glomeruli, seminal vesicles, decidual cells and salivary glands were in general negative.

Several cases of thyroid, lung and prostate cancers along with a few colorectal, ovarian, urothelial, liver and uterine cervical cancers displayed moderate to strong staining. Remaining tumor cells were in general negative.

tissueExpression.summary: Subset cells of gastrointestinal tract, gall bladder, renal tubules, cells in seminiferus ducts and glandular cells of cervix displayed moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Remaining normal tissues were weakly stained or negative.
Rare breast, testis and urothelial cancers exhibited moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Remaining cancer tissues were weakly stained or negative.
